article.description: T.J. Cromer scored 23 points and dished out seven assists to lead East Tennessee State to a 78-68 win over Morehead State on Saturday.
article.headline: E. Tennessee St. coasts behind Cromer's 23 points
article.linkText: E. Tennessee St. coasts behind Cromer's 23 points
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. -- T.J. Cromer scored 23 points and dished out seven assists to lead East Tennessee State to a 78-68 win over Morehead State on Saturday. The Buccaneers have won back-to-back games following a 14-point loss to Dayton, and have won seven of eight overall. Cromer did much of his damage from behind the arc, drilling 6 of 9 from long range. Desonta Bradford and Hanner Mosquera-Perea each finished with 13 points for East Tennessee State (9-2). The Buccaneers shot 50 percent from the field while holding the Eagles to just 32.4 percent. Xavier Moon led Morehead State (2-8) with 19 points, while DeJuan Marrero added 17. The Eagles have lost eight consecutive games. Cromer hit a 3 to spark a 12-2 East Tennessee State run to start the game, and the Bucs led by 15 at the break. The Eagles got as close as eight in the second, but never seriously threatened. The game was the first for Morehead State following the resignation of head coach Sean Woods on Thursday, two days after being charged with misdemeanor battery in Indiana. Two players accused him of assaulting them during a game. Woods had been suspended since Nov. 22. Preston Spradlin, an assistant on Woods' staff, is serving as interim head coach.
